#### **Solution A(a): 4-to-1 MUX — Dataflow (7 marks)**

**Truth Table:**

| sel(1) | sel(0) | y |
|:---:|:---:|:---:|
| 0 | 0 | d(0) |
| 0 | 1 | d(1) |
| 1 | 0 | d(2) |
| 1 | 1 | d(3) |

**Boolean Expression:**

$$
y = \bar{s_1}\bar{s_0}d_0 + \bar{s_1}s_0 d_1 + s_1\bar{s_0}d_2 + s_1 s_0 d_3
$$

**VHDL Code (Dataflow):**

```vhdl
LIBRARY ieee;
USE ieee.std_logic_1164.all;

ENTITY mux4to1 IS
    PORT ( d   : IN  STD_LOGIC_VECTOR(3 DOWNTO 0);
           sel : IN  STD_LOGIC_VECTOR(1 DOWNTO 0);
           y   : OUT STD_LOGIC);
END mux4to1;

ARCHITECTURE dataflow OF mux4to1 IS
BEGIN
    y <= d(0) WHEN sel = "00" ELSE
         d(1) WHEN sel = "01" ELSE
         d(2) WHEN sel = "10" ELSE
         d(3);
END dataflow;
```

**Mark distribution:**
- Truth table (2 marks)
- Boolean expression (1 mark)
- VHDL code with library and entity (3 marks)
- Architecture with `when-else` (1 mark)

