#### **Solution B(b): Moore Sequence Detector "101" (7 marks)**

**State Diagram Description:**
- **S0** (Initial / No match): On `din='1'`, go to S1. On `din='0'`, stay in S0.
- **S1** (Seen "1"): On `din='0'`, go to S2. On `din='1'`, stay in S1.
- **S2** (Seen "10"): On `din='1'`, go to S3. On `din='0'`, stay in S2.
- **S3** (Seen "101" — Output = 1): On `din='1'`, go to S1 (overlap). On `din='0'`, go to S2.

**State Transition Table:**

| Present State | Input din = 0 | Input din = 1 | Output |
|---|---|---|---|
| S0 | S0 | S1 | 0 |
| S1 | S2 | S1 | 0 |
| S2 | S2 | S3 | 0 |
| S3 | S2 | S1 | 1 |

**VHDL Code:**

```vhdl
LIBRARY ieee;
USE ieee.std_logic_1164.all;

ENTITY moore_101 IS
    PORT ( clk, rst, din : IN  STD_LOGIC;
           dout           : OUT STD_LOGIC);
END moore_101;

ARCHITECTURE behavioral OF moore_101 IS
    TYPE state_t IS (S0, S1, S2, S3);
    SIGNAL ps, ns : state_t;
BEGIN
    -- State register
    PROCESS (clk, rst)
    BEGIN
        IF rst = '1' THEN
            ps <= S0;
        ELSIF clk'EVENT AND clk = '1' THEN
            ps <= ns;
        END IF;
    END PROCESS;

    -- Next-state logic
    PROCESS (ps, din)
    BEGIN
        CASE ps IS
            WHEN S0 =>
                IF din = '1' THEN ns <= S1; ELSE ns <= S0; END IF;
            WHEN S1 =>
                IF din = '0' THEN ns <= S2; ELSE ns <= S1; END IF;
            WHEN S2 =>
                IF din = '1' THEN ns <= S3; ELSE ns <= S2; END IF;
            WHEN S3 =>
                IF din = '1' THEN ns <= S1; ELSE ns <= S2; END IF;
        END CASE;
    END PROCESS;

    -- Output logic (Moore)
    PROCESS (ps)
    BEGIN
        CASE ps IS
            WHEN S3 => dout <= '1';
            WHEN OTHERS => dout <= '0';
        END CASE;
    END PROCESS;
END behavioral;
```

**Mark distribution:**
- State diagram and transition table (2 marks)
- Type declaration and signal declarations (1 mark)
- State register process (1 mark)
- Next-state logic with all 4 states (2 marks)
- Moore output process (1 mark)

