### 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

- [x] **VHDL = VHSIC Hardware Description Language**, IEEE Std 1076.
- [x] Always start with `LIBRARY ieee; USE ieee.std_logic_1164.all;` and `USE ieee.numeric_std.all;` for arithmetic.
- [x] Use `STD_LOGIC` and `STD_LOGIC_VECTOR` (NOT `BIT`).
- [x] **Entity** = interface; **Architecture** = internal logic.
- [x] Three modeling styles: **Dataflow** (concurrent `<=`, `when-else`, `with-select`), **Behavioral** (`process` + `if/case`), **Structural** (`component` + `port map`).
- [x] **Concurrent** statements run in parallel; **Sequential** statements (inside `process`) run in order.
- [x] **Sensitivity list** must contain all inputs read inside a combinational `process`.
- [x] **Clock edge detection:** `clk'EVENT AND clk = '1'` (or `RISING_EDGE(clk)`).
- [x] **Asynchronous reset:** `rst` and `clk` both in sensitivity list; reset check first.
- [x] **Synchronous reset/enable:** only `clk` triggers; reset/enable checked inside `if` after edge.
- [x] Use `UNSIGNED` (from `numeric_std`) for arithmetic; convert to `STD_LOGIC_VECTOR` for output.
- [x] Always include `WHEN OTHERS` in `with-select` and `CASE` for synthesis.
- [x] **Moore** output = `f(state)`; **Mealy** output = `f(state, input)`.
- [x] Mealy FSM uses fewer states; Moore output is glitch-free and synchronized.
- [x] Signal assignment inside process: use `<=`; variable assignment: use `:=` (variables are local to process).
- [x] Aggregated assignment: `y <= (OTHERS => '0');` clears all bits.
- [x] Concatenation: `a & b` joins bits/vectors; slicing: `x(3 DOWNTO 0)` selects a portion.
- [x] Component instantiation requires a label: `LABEL : component_name PORT MAP (...);`.
- [x] Ring counter and Johnson counter are shift-register-based counters commonly asked.
- [x] BCD counter wraps at `"1001"`; up/down counter has a direction control signal.
- [x] Common errors: missing sensitivity entries, missing `OTHERS`, mixing `:=`/`<=`, using `BIT` instead of `STD_LOGIC`.

